data.name: Holy Land Bakery, Grocery and Deli
data.description: over 25 years of excellence our award winning restaurant has been serving the twin cities with the best meddle eastern food using Mama Fatima original recipes , and providing them with the largest selections of fresh bread , olives , cheeses , olive oil and finest imported grocery items , our meat department offers all 100% grass fed lamb , goat and beef with the highest quality available in the market (best of the best ) all HALAL-ZABIHA CERTIFIED.

data.name: Wood + Paddle Eatery
data.description: The dishes at Wood + Paddle Eatery are crafted into menus that satisfy different appetites and tastes, catering to just about every occasion, from every day to special days. Our skills and indeed our culture are deeply rooted in North American food and service with a great influence from the Midwest. Simply great tastes in a great space - all delivered with great service, a big heart and an even bigger smile. Locally Grown, Perfectly Seasoned.
data.address: 31 S 7th St Royal Sonesta Minneapolis Downtown, Minneapolis, MN 55402

photo.caption: Yup, that little tiny house is what all the fuss is about :)

data.name: The Capital Grille
data.description: Make it a day to remember. From birthdays and anniversaries to professional milestones, we aim to make every gathering special at The Capital Grille. Open seven days a week, The Capital Grille is best known for our expertly prepared steaks, which are dry aged in house for 18 to 24 days and then hand-cut by our restaurant's on-premise butcher. The Capital Grille's wine list features more than 350 selections, and its floor-to-ceiling wine kiosk regularly houses 3,500 - 5,000 bottles. Reservations are recommended but not required. For more information, please visit our website. We look forward to delighting you.
data.address: 801 Hennepin Ave State Theatre, Minneapolis, MN 55402-1818

data.name: Red Cow North Loop
data.description: Casual & rustic American eatery offering craft beer, gourmet burgers & a menu of updated pub eats.

data.name: Zelo
data.description: At Zelo, we serve simple, fresh Italian cuisine made from local ingredients. Our handcrafted meals accompany a thoughtful, approachable wine selection. We believe dining is more than a menu: it is an experience, and ours is quality. When you’re our guest, our staff learn your name and remember your favorite glass of wine. We passionately commit to bring you the full dining experience – quality food and wine presented with welcoming service. Every meal. Every day. An enduring Minneapolis destination, Zelo was opened in 1999 by Rick Webb, a Minnesota restaurateur whose pursuits have set the standard in Twin Cities dining for over 40 years. Looking for another unparalleled dining experience in the south metro? Visit Rick Webb’s acclaimed Ciao Bella, the restaurant that inspired Zelo’s handcrafted food and dedicated service.
data.address: 831 Nicollet Mall Medical Arts Building, Minneapolis, MN 55402-2506

data.name: Tullibee
data.description: Tullibee's restaurant and bar are inspired by the bounty of Minnesota's woods & lakes. We pay tribute with a menu influenced by practices of foraging, butchery, and fermentation techniques while being heavily driven by seasonality. Helmed by Chef Matt Leverty.

data.name: Murray's
data.description: Established in 1946, our family owned and operated Steakhouse is sure to impress. Priding ourselves on the fine dining and cocktail lounge experience, our delectable menu and professional service will keep you coming back. Located conveniently downtown near all of your favorite theaters, our lunch or happy hour is perfect for any occasion! Come see us today!

data.name: Cafe Lurcat
data.description: Café & Bar Lurcat is a hip, urban venue that boasts serious food and voguish design. Enjoy the floor to ceiling windows with breathtaking views overlooking Loring Park. This historic property features beautiful brick work, checkered tile floors, and nine crystal chandeliers. Our bar and lounge is the perfect setting for your wedding ceremony and reception. We can accommodate seated meals for up to 180 guests and cocktail style receptions up to 200. We also have additional options for smaller wedding events too. Our private dining room seats 50-55 guests and includes our beautiful back patio space. This is a great option for a rehearsal dinner too. Café & Bar Lurcat is a perfect blend of classic old world style with a Nouveau twist.

data.name: Pizzeria Lola
data.description: A Korean immigrant, inspired by the pure love of food, joy and her mother’s own delicious cooking, quits her day job, opens an artisan pizza pie place and names it after her dog. Yep, sometimes dreams do come true! Pizzeria Lola is a family-friendly pizzeria located in South Minneapolis. We offer award-winning wood fire pizzas, delicious sides, warm cookies & soft serve, beer, wine, and cocktails. What's not to like? Pizzeria Lola has been featured on Netflix's Chef's Table: Pizza, Food Network's Diners, Drive-Ins and Dives and CBS Saturday and in national publications including the New York Times, Forbes, Wall Street Journal and Food & Wine (to name a few) Reservations are available and walk-ins are always welcome!

data.name: Surly Brewing Company
data.description: Surly’s Beer Hall and Beer Garden is officially re-opening. Here’s what’s what: We're starting with beer service and the Surly food truck. Guests will find 20 tap lines that include core brands like Furious and Grapefruit Supreme, beer hall-only styles such as Rose and specialty kegs of port barrel-aged stout and Crucial Cream Ale. The Surly food truck will make its triumphant return with classic can’t-miss sandwiches, including brisket and pulled pork. This is the first phase of reopening. Our full kitchen, Surly Pizza, and events center will follow in the coming months. The most up-to-date details will be shared on Instagram at SurlyBeerHall.

data.name: Broders’ Pasta Bar
data.description: Since 1994 Broders' Pasta Bar has been serving house made and quality imported pastas and risottos, focusing both on Italian regional traditions as well as seasonal & local ingredients. We source from Midwest farms, when possible, and grow vegetables in our own parking lot garden (weather permitting, of course!) but really, it's about the pasta. Located across W. 50th Street from Broders’ Cucina Italiana, the original deli and specialty food shop, Molly and Tom Broder opened the Pasta Bar - to cook the pasta they were selling the way it was meant to be: fresh, al dente, perfectly sauced and thoughtfully executed. Still, and always, family owned and operated, Broders' continually strives to serve great Italian food and wine from our corner in Southwest Minneapolis. We hope to welcome you, whether at the Cucina, Pasta Bar, or the newest addition, Terzo, our contemporary Italian restaurant & wine bar. Saluti!

data.name: Manny's Steakhouse

photo.caption: An intimidating 14 oz. Filet Mignon, excellent in cut and flavor --no need for the Hollandaise

data.description: Masculine, bright, accented with wood & leather, Manny's evokes the great steakhouses of New York & Chicago - & eclipses them in critical & popular acclaim. Rated Top Five in the U.S. by the Zagat Guide, named one of America's top Steakhouses by the Knife & Fork Club, Men's Journal & the Independent Cattleman's Association, & a perennial winner of newspaper & magazine reader polls, Manny's commands a fanatical local following & a national reputation. Wrote the New York Times: "There's good news in Minneapolis for those who still share the secret pleasures of red meat, well-cut & seriously served." In addition to USDA-certified, dry- aged, center-cut beef, Manny's offers chops, chicken, fresh seafood & a Wine Spectator Award-winning wine list.

data.name: Alma
data.description: We are a cafe, restaurant & boutique hotel. Since 1999 we have welcomed guests with genuine hospitality and diverse American cooking. We strive to create beautiful, casual environments worthy of everyday visits & celebrations. Our daytime cafe features elevated, casual cooking and bakery. The restaurant is a dinner only, seasonally inspired prix fixe concept, and the boutique hotel offers beautiful, one of a kind rooms. Alma has received local and national acclaim, including a 4-star review from the StarTribune, a James Beard Foundation Award for "Best Chef Midwest", and multiple JBF national semifinal nominations in both "Outstanding Service" and "Outstanding Restaurant", and "Outstanding Chef" categories.

data.name: Fogo de Chao Brazilian Steakhouse

photo.caption: Picanha: Prime part of the Top Sirloin. Lightly seasoned with rock salt & sliced thin

data.description: Fogo de Chão is an internationally-renowned steakhouse from Brazil that allows guests to discover what's next at every turn. Founded in Southern Brazil in 1979, Fogo elevates the centuries-old culinary art of churrasco - roasting high-quality cuts of meat over an open flame - into a cultural dining experience of discovery. Please join us in our dining room, in our more casual Bar Fogo, or bring the Fogo Experience to you with Fogo To-Go or Catering. Visit our website to make a reservation or place an order.
